 written by Adobe Photoshop'),(4559,166,2,7,0,'Photo'),(1762,85,3,74,0,'8'),(4542,82,2,41,0,'This is an example of a modern letterpress. In a broader spectrum, letterpress fits into a type of printing known as relief printing. In relief there exist two materials, the matrix and the substrate. The matrix can be made of wood, metal, linoleum, or any other surface that can hold ink. The substrate is the material which the matrix is being printed on, such as paper or fabric. The matrix is inked up and everything that is not recessed will collect ink. Pressure is applied to the substrate on top of the matrix and the reverse image is printed to the surface. The key to letterpress and other forms of printing are editions, multiple copies of the same image quality. - Michael Snowadzky'),(4541,82,2,49,0,'Graphic Design (Typography)'),(4564,179,3,73,0,'575'),(4565,179,3,72,0,'972'),(4566,167,2,50,0,'Default Neatline Map'),(4567,167,2,39,0,'Mateusz Gwizdala'),(4568,167,2,40,0,'28 November 2012'),(4551,178,3,76,0,'FileName:47f69f788dae862cd834f7a0cee6005a.jpg\nFileDateTime:1354132147\nFileSize:101113\nFileType:2\nMimeType:image/jpeg\nSectionsFound:\nCOMPUTED:\n	html:width=\"665\" height=\"549\"\n	Height:549\n	Width:665\n	IsColor:1\n\n'),(4552,178,3,73,0,'549'),(4553,178,3,72,0,'665'),(4558,166,2,42,0,'Image'),(4550,178,3,77,0,'a:7:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"47f69f788dae862cd834f7a0cee6005a.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1354132147;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:101113;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:4:{s:4:\"html\";s:24:\"width=\"665\" height=\"549\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:549;s:5:\"Width\";i:665;s:7:\"IsColor\";i:1;}}'),(1763,85,3,73,0,'53'),(1764,85,3,72,0,'209'),(2970,80,2,49,0,'Graphic Design (Typography)'),(2969,80,2,50,0,'Seriph'),(2978,79,2,50,0,'Typography Theory: Design Considerations'),(1784,87,3,74,0,'8'),(1785,87,3,73,0,'600'),(1786,87,3,72,0,'500'),(3739,86,2,40,0,'1858'),(3740,86,2,37,0,'Pablohoney77'),(374