INSERT INTO `omeka_exhibits` VALUES (2,'The Basics','<p><img src=\"http://dh101.humanities.ucla.edu/DH101Fall12Lab1/archive/files/351b64c9a11be14ad1f6f83994ca7d0f.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>In <em>Elements of Typographic Style</em>, Robert Bringhurst once described Typography as \"<span>the craft of endowing human language with a durable visual form\".</span>&nbsp;Typography undoubtedly plays a fundamental role in our understanding of written language; but, what of the language the field of typography carries within itself?</p>\r\n<p>Like any discipline, the study of typography has a unique vernacular. While most books and websites on type <em>do</em> offer glossaries and appendices, at first glance, these overviews can pose a daunting challenge to budding typophiles. Here one finds an exhibit consisting, in simple terms, of some basic typography concepts we&nbsp;think would equip beginners &nbsp;with the tools necessary to move on to more advanced discussion and practice.</p>\r\n<p>Topics currently include: Typeface Anatomy, Typeface Classification</p>\r\n<p>Proposed future topics: Font Families, Text Arrangement, Grid.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Users will also find a \"Resources\" page that links several educational tools for further exploration of the concepts introduced.&nbsp;</p>','Iman Salehian',0,1,'','a:1:{s:7:\"default\";a:4:{s:4:\"logo\";s:36:\"7cbdcab863cabe1053766a80a026fde5.jpg\";s:17:\"header_background\";N;s:11:\"footer_text\";s:0:\"\";s:24:\"display_footer_copyright\";s:1:\"0\";}}','basics'),(4,'Typography: A History','<p><img src=\"http://dh101.humanities.ucla.edu/DH101Fall12Lab1/archive/files/d637c733d1cd1a7fbafafe4c4988bda9.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Contemporary typographers view typography as craft with a very long&nbsp;<a>history&nbsp;</a>tracing its origins back to the first punches and dies used to make&nbsp;<a>seals&nbsp;</a>and&nbsp;<a>currency&nbsp;</a>in&nbsp;ancient times. The basic elements of typography are at least as old as&nbsp;<a>civilization and</a> the earliest&nbsp;writing systems&mdash;a series of key developments that were eventually drawn together as a systematic craft.</p>','Wikipedia, www.hrc.utexas.edu',0,1,'default',NULL,'typography--a-history'),(8,'Methodology','<p>In order to add an overarching level of transparency to our critical resource, this exhibit provides users with a description of our process- including issues faced, solutions found, proposed areas of improval, and more.</p>\r\n<p>Each sections has been authored by an individual group member according to their area of focus.&nbsp;</p>','',0,1,'',NULL,'methodology'),(7,'Learning about Typography','<p><img src=\"http://dh101.humanities.ucla.edu/DH101Fall12Lab1/archive/files/99525cc449cce9c5b07f7db287c8f105.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><span>Students of typography/letterfaces/typefonts/type in classroom environments use more online resources than other traditional fields of study: humanities, social sceinces, sciences. It might be because the nature of the medium is the web today (there are plenty of typographers per se, but most students are taught and aspire to be graphic designers).</span></p>\r\n<p>The following syllabi are treated as both a resource for autodidacts and amateur typographers, but also as tools that&nbsp;\"reveal a network of trends over geographies, time and disciplines, mapping which texts and authors are in favor\" (Morgan Currie).</p>\r\n<p><span><br /></span></p>','Leon de Santillana',0,1,'',NULL,'resources');
